    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Dialog: View References</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;">Show Element References</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Delete-DependentElements">Delete Dependent Elements</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Many elements reference, or need, other elements.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Show Element References</text><text styleclass="Interface2"> </text>lists those elements that a more complex element needs to build</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="4" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-SW-Show-Element-References.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption>Selection--Window: Right-Click</caption></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">To see the <text styleclass="VariableName">Element References</text> for an element:</para>
          <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI Semibold'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Click an <text styleclass="Element">Element</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Graphics-Area</text> or the <text styleclass="Interface">Assembly-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Right-click the <text styleclass="Element">element</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Selection-Window</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Click <text styleclass="VariableName">Show Element References</text> in the <text styleclass="Body Text">shortcut menu</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Body Text">The </text><text styleclass="VariableName">List References for: element-name</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> shows.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-Dialog-Element-References.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption>Element References interface</caption></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">The pop-up shows the: </para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">Reference Element name</text></li>
            <li styleclass="VariableName-indent">Number(?) </li>
            <li styleclass="VariableName-indent">Reference Element Type</li>
            <li styleclass="VariableName-indent">Reference Element Owner</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">For example, w<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">hen you add a </text><text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">, you select two </text><text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> in two different </text><text styleclass="Element">Parts</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">. Thus, the </text><text styleclass="Element">Pin-Joint</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> references the two </text><text styleclass="Element">Points </text>that are owned by the <text styleclass="Element">Parts.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
